<center><h2><font size=+3>T</font>he <font size=+3>H</font>eritage <font size=+3>F</font>oundation</h2></center>
<center><h3><font size=+2>P</font>ublications <font size=+2>L</font>ibrary</h3>
<hr size=3 width=50%>
<p>
<b>Economic and Political Theory: Economics 
</b>
</center>
<p>
<ul>
<b>Books:</b>
<p>
<a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/1980s.html">What Really Happened
 in the 1980s?</a> by Peter J. Ferrara. (<i>Issues '94: The Candidate's Briefing
 Book</i>)
<p>
<b>Policy Papers:</b>
<p>
<li>1/23/97 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/bg1100.html">Energizing America: A Blueprint for Deregulating the Electricity Market</a> by <A HREF="/heritage/staff/thierer.htm">Adam D. Thierer</A>. (Backgrounder #1100)
<li>12/16/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/bg1093.html">How A Flat Tax Would Affect Charitable Contributions</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/barry.html">John S. Barry</a>. (Backgrounder #1093)
<li>10/7/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/fyi121.html">Feeling the Pinch: Why Income Gains Remain Elusive for Many American Families</a> by  <a href="/heritage/staff/wilson.htm">Mark Wilson</a>. (F.Y.I. #121)
<li>9/10/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/em459.html">Government's Hidden Tax: Time to Account for the Cost of Regulation</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/antonel.htm">Angela Antonelli</a>.  (Executive Memorandum #459)

