<b>Regulations and Infrastructure: Telecommunications 
</b>
</center>
<p>
<ul>
<b>Books:</b>
<p>
<a href="/heritage/congress/chapt3.html">How the 104th Congress Cut  Red Tape and Returned Common Sense to Regulation</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/antonel.htm">Angela Antonelli</a>. (<i>Reviewing the Revolution: Conservative Successes in the 104th Congress</i>)<p>
<b>Policy Papers:</b>
<p>
<li>6/7/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/bg1085.html">Senator Pressler's Bold Proposal for Spectrum Freedom</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/thierer.htm">Adam Thierer</a>.  (Backgrounder No. 1085)


<li>5/20/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/em450.html">How to Improve the Quality of Children's Television</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/thierer.htm">Adam Thierer</a>. (Executive Memorandum #450)
<li>3/19/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/tp11.html">A Policy Maker's Guide To Deregulating Telecommunications Part 6: A Free-Market Future For Spectrum</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/thierer.htm">Adam Thierer</a>. (Talking Points #11)
<li>1/23/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/fyi84.html">How the Telecom Bill Gives Away $70 Billion in Family Tax Relief to the Broadcast Industry</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/thierer.htm">Adam Thierer</a> (F.Y.I. #84)
<li>9/7/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/bg1052.html">The Voice of America: Don't Silence America's Voice in the Global Marketplace of Ideas</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/feulner.html">Edwin J. Feulner, Jr.</a> and Thomas G. Moore. (Backgrounder #1052)
<li>7/11/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/bgup255.html">Improving the House Telecommunications Plan (H.R. 1555)</a> by Adam Thierer. (Backgrounder Update #255, Updating Issue Bulletin #209, "A Report Card on the Pressler Telecommunications Plan (S. 652)", May 5, 1995)
<li>5/23/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/em414.html">How To Solve the CBO's Telecom Tax Problem</a> by Adam D. Thierer. (Executive Memorandum #414)
<li>5/5/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/ib209.html">A Report Card on the Pressler Telecommunications Plan</a> by Adam D. Thierer. (Issue Bulletin #209)
<li>8/24/94 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/bgu233.html">Senator Dole's Welcome Proposal for Telecommunications Freedom</a> by Adam D. Thierer. (Backgrounder Update #233)
<li>10/29/93 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/em368.html">Why the Fairness Doctrine is Anything But Fair</a> by Adam Thierer. (Executive Memorandum #368)
<li>3/4/91 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/em297.html"
>How the Federal Government Contributes to Poor Quality TV Programs</a> by William G. Laffer III. (Executive Memorandum #297)
<p></ul>
