<FONT SIZE=+2>ANNUAL MEETING
</FONT>
<P>

	December 15, 1995 is the date for the Annual Meeting of Americans for Tax Reform (ATR).<P>
	Any member who wishes to nominate an individual to serve as a director of ATR should submit a nomination at least 60 days prior to that date.<P>
	As stated in the ATR bylaws, any nomination must be submitted in writing and signed by five nominators who are members in good standing of the association.<P>
	The nominee receiving the most votes of regular members voting shall be duly declared, elected, and installed as the regular-member class director.<P>
