<TITLE>Conservative Cartoon Club</TITLE>
</head>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">
<P>
<center>
<P>
<img src="/townhall/infotain/humor/ccc/spot.gif">
<P>

<h2>
Membership Agreement
</h2>
<P>
</center>
<blockquote>
ONE YEAR MEMBERSHIP -- $15.00 (U.S. Dollars)<br>
FREE use of cartoons to Club Members
<P><blockquote>
Robert S. Clark owns exclusive copyright to all Conservative Cartoon Club cartoons, and 
grants to current and paid-up Club Members FREE non-exclusive reprint rights to all 
Conservative Cartoon Club cartoons (to over 200 cartoons in a 12 month period) 
according to the terms of this membership agreement.  Club Member may use and reuse 
Conservative Club cartoons in Club Member's publication, (broadside, newsletter, 
newspaper, magazine, etc.).  Club Member may also use and reuse Conservative Club 
cartoons to net up to $500.00 per month, selling items with Conservative Cartoon Club 
cartoons printed on them (T-shirts, posters, greeting cards, calendars, etc.).  Neither the 
Conservative Cartoon Club nor Robert S. Clark will be responsible for losses, taxes, fees, 
permits, debts, judgments, etc., incurred by Club Member as a result of Club Member's 
use of Conservative Cartoon Club cartoons.  All Conservative Cartoon Club cartoons 
used by Club Member must bear proper copyright notice, Conservative Cartoon Club 
Logo and current Internet address.  Club Member cannot transfer copyright and/or grant 
the right to use Conservative Cartoon Club cartoons to others.  Club Member cannot 
compile Conservative Club cartoons into book form for the purpose of publication.  With 
the exceptions of reducing or enlarging in whole, adding color without distorting artwork 
or text, and translating words into another language keeping original intent - no other 
alterations of Conservative Cartoon Club cartoons are permitted.  This membership may 
be cancelled at any time by either Robert S. Clark or Club Member.  If cancelled, any 
unused months of membership fee will be returned to Club Member.  Membership must 
be cancelled within 30 days in order to receive refund.  Conservative Cartoon Club 
cartoons are provided to Club Members via Town Hall on the Internet.  The Town Hall 
Internet address is http://www.townhall.com
<P>
To join the Club, call or mail the following:
<P>
One year membership <br>
$15.00 (U.S.) payable to:<br>
Robert S. Clark<br>
<P>
send to:<br>
Conservative Cartoon Club<br>
203 Lohmann Street<br>
Boerne, TX  78006-2031<br>
<P>
or call:<br>
(210) 816-9668<br>
