<HEAD>
<TITLE>Medical Innovation Project -- PFF</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="backgrnd.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"  LINK="#8C1717" VLINK="#545454" ALINK="#FF0000">
<map name="wst">
<area shape="rect" coords="0,0,92,20" href="#works">
<area shape="rect" coords="93,0,193,20" href="#speeches">
<area shape="rect" coords="194,0,318,20" href="#testimonies"></map>

<ul><blockquote>

<a href="welcome.html"><img src="bi.gif" align="right" border="0" alt="PFF"></a>
<center>
<a href="wst.map"><img src="wst.gif" border="0" USEMAP="#wst" ISMAP></a>
<img src="miphead.gif" alt="Medical Innovation Project">
</center>
<br><br><P>
<table>
<tr>
<td valign="top" width="20%">
Surgical Lasers!  Genetic Engineering!  Molecular Transports!
 Surgery in Cyberspace!  Civilization is poised to make major
strides in medicine and health.  These advances have the potential
to dramatically increase both life spans and the quality of life,
while at the same time reducing the cost of health care.
<P>
Yet America's enjoyment of these benefits is threatened because
every day the current system for approving new medical technology
stays in place is another day Americans die needless deaths and
suffer senseless pain.   Why is that many of our drug and medical
device companies are able to offer products to patients in Europe
years before they ever receive FDA approval to do in the USA?
 How do we speed the approval process while ensuring safety? 
Who should pay for all this?  Is it time to replace the FDA?
<td valign="top">
<a name="works"></a>
<img src="bullet.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><big>Works</big>
<ul>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><a href="/pff/mip/len051496.html">Real Reform or Pilot Programs?</a>
 by Thomas Lenard.<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><b>Advancing Medical Innovation: <a href="/pff/mip/fdatoc.html">Health, Safety, and the Role of Government in the 21st Century</a></b> by Ralph Epstein, Thomas Lenard, Henry Miller, Robert Tollison, W. Kip Viscusi, and William Wardell<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><b>The Future of Medical Innovation: <a href="new-approach-med.html">A New Approach For Bringing Medical Products to Market</a></b> by Thomas Lenard, Ralph Epstein, Robert Tollison, W. Kip Viscusi and William M. Wardell <br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><b>The Future of Medical Innovation: <a href="tom4.html">Reaping the Benefits of the Knowledge Revolution</a></b> by Thomas Lenard and Brian Mannix<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><a href="/pff/mip/pr020796.html"><b>Plan Kicks off FDA Reform</a></b>
</ul>
<a name="speeches"></a>

<img src="bullet.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><big>Speeches</big>
<ul>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" aling="top"><a href="/pff/mip/teske042596.html"><b>How Conservatives Can Win The Coming Medicade Debate</b></a>: Speech by Richard Teske.<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" aling="top"><a href="/pff/mip/esen0323.html"><b>FDA Reform</b></a>: Comments by Foundation President Jeff Eisenach on ABC's Nightline.<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" aling="top"><a href="/pff/mip/blil0208.html"><b>Medical Innovation Conference Remarks</a></b> by Chairman Thomas Bliley.<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><a href="/pff/mip/rath0207.html"><b>Medical Innovation Conference Remarks</b></a> by Dr. George Rathmann<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><a href="/pff/mip/sull0207.html"><b>Regulating Medical Technology in the 21st Century</b></a> by Dr. Louis Sullivan<br>
<img src="diamond.gif" hspace="5" align="top"><a href="amciv/ac-july/ac795wh.html"><b>Treating Illness Before It Occurs and Other Marvels of Modern Medicine</a></b> by William Haseltine<br>
