<head>
<title>LI-Broadcast Journalism School</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<img src="/lead-inst/sc-logo.gif"><p>
<h2>Broadcast Journalism School</h2>
<center><a href="http://www.townhall.com/lead-inst/bjsclips.ram">Listen to recommendations from BJS Students</a> <img src="/lead-inst/ra.gif"></center><P>
<center><b>Internet Applicants receive $25 discount on registration</b></center>
</center>
<pre><b>
			1996
			Washington, DC	- October 19-20
			Regent University - December 7-8

			1997
			Arlington, VA - March 7-8
			Arlington, VA - June 21-22
			Arlington, VA - August 2-3
			Tulsa, OK - September 27-28
			Arlington, VA - October 25-26
			Virginia Beach, VA - December 6-7		
</b></pre><p>
From winning an internship to landing full-time employment in TV or radio, the Broadcast Journalism School gives you crucial information your college can't.
<p>
Led by experts who work in the news media, this school teaches you how to prepare yourself for a career in this liberal-dominated field.  Sessions include how to:<br>
<ul>
<b>
<font size=+1>
<li>Secure jobs in the highly competitive journalism field 
<li>Make your resume stand out from the rest
<li>Advance your career once you land your first job
<li>Impact newscasts from important off-air jobs
<li>Cope with the liberal bias of co-workers
</b>
</font>
</ul>
<p>
<center>
<b>For more information contact Amy Morris at 1-800-827-LEAD or fax (703) 247-2001</b>
<p>
